JSTRICK

A simple code to demonstrate how to improve your skills on string replacements
using Javascript

str_replace is a prototype function that can be attached to your application
in order to improve your way to apply text replacements on strings

HOW TO USE

let s be your string.

<code>

var s = "I love %0, %1 and %2 for breakfast";
console.log(s.str_replace(["oat","milk","honey"]));

// output
"I love oat, milk and honey."

// but you can put replacers in sorted order
var s = "I love %2, %0 and %1 for breakfast";
console.log(s.str_replace(["banana","milk","honey"]));

// output2
"I love honey, oat and milk for breakfast"


</code>